@page "/portfolio"

<PageTitle>mattopie.com - Portfolio</PageTitle>
<div class="headers">
    <h1>Matt Opie - Portfolio</h1>
</div>

<div class="project-container card">
    <div class="project-title">
        <div>
            <a class="project-link" href="/" target="_blank">
                <h4>mattopie.com</h4>
            </a><a class="git-link" href="https://www.github.com/matthew-opie/blazor-portfolio-2026/" target="_blank"><i class="fa-brands fa-github"></i>Github</a>
        </div>
        <img class="project-image" src="/images/website-screenshot.png" alt=""/>
    </div>

    <div class="project-description">
        <p>A personal website built for experimenting with new ideas.</p>
        <p>
            Built on .NET 10 Blazor WebAssembly — chosen for strongly-typed C# code-behind over a JavaScript framework.
            Deployed automatically to AWS S3 via GitHub Actions on every push to main, with Cloudflare handling DNS and free-tier edge caching.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="project-tags">
        <div class="tags-label">
            <p>Technologies used:</p>
            <ul class="tag-group">
                <li class="tag">.NET Blazor</li>
                <li class="tag">HTML5</li>
                <li class="tag">CSS3</li>
                <li class="tag">AWS S3 Buckets</li>
                <li class="tag">Github Actions</li>
                <li class="tag">Cloudflare DNS</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="project-container card">
    <div class="project-title">
        <div>
            <a class="project-link" href="/pomodoro">
                <h4>Tomato Timer</h4>
            </a>
        </div>
        <img class="project-image" src="/images/pomodoro-screenshot.png"/>
    </div>

    <div class="project-description">
        <p>A productivity-focused timer based on the Pomodoro Technique.</p>
        <p>
            Features three independent timers — Focus, Short Break, and Long Break — each running in their own
            state with animated progress rings and color-coded themes. Browser notifications and the Vibration API
            fire on completion. A session dot tracker counts completed pomodoros and auto-suggests the next break type.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="project-tags">
        <div class="tags-label">
            <p>Technologies used:</p>
            <ul class="tag-group">
                <li class="tag">.NET Blazor</li>
                <li class="tag">C#</li>
                <li class="tag">JS Interop</li>
                <li class="tag">Web Notifications API</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="project-container card">
    <div class="project-title">
        <div>
            <a class="project-link" href="/typing">
                <h4>Typing Speed Test</h4>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="project-description">
        <p>A live WPM typing test built around passages from public domain literature.</p>
        <p>
            Passages are loaded from an external JSON file and shuffled into a non-repeating queue each session.
            Text is scored character-by-character in real time with green/red feedback per keystroke. The test ends
            when the passage is complete or the 60-second timer expires, then reports WPM, accuracy, and elapsed time.
            Backspace support allows correcting the previous word mid-test.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="project-tags">
        <div class="tags-label">
            <p>Technologies used:</p>
            <ul class="tag-group">
                <li class="tag">.NET Blazor</li>
                <li class="tag">C#</li>
                <li class="tag">JS Interop</li>
                <li class="tag">JSON</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="project-container card">
    <div class="project-title">
        <div>
            <a class="project-link" href="/markdown">
                <h4>Markdown Previewer</h4>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="project-description">
        <p>A live split-pane Markdown editor with instant HTML preview.</p>
        <p>
            Renders Markdown to HTML in real time using the Markdig library with the CommonMark spec, supporting
            tables, fenced code blocks, task lists, and autolinks. A toolbar provides one-click insertion of common
            syntax at the cursor position with selected text wrapping. Includes a live word and character counter
            and a Copy HTML button.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="project-tags">
        <div class="tags-label">
            <p>Technologies used:</p>
            <ul class="tag-group">
                <li class="tag">.NET Blazor</li>
                <li class="tag">C#</li>
                <li class="tag">Markdig</li>
                <li class="tag">JS Interop</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
